   disorders) based on motion recognition technologies. To address these
   issues, in the current work, we propose an end-to-end abnormal behaviour
   detection framework from a new perspective in conjunction with the Graph
   Convolutional Network (GCN) and a 3D Convolutional Neural Network
   (3DCNN). Specifically, we first train a one-class classifier to extract
   features and estimate abnormality scores. To improve the performance of
   abnormal behavior detection, GCN is used to model the similarity between
